---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Contribute" canonicalPath="/contribute/">
  <header class="page-head narrow"><p class="eyebrow">Contribute evidence</p><h1>A registry entry begins with a primary source.</h1><p class="lede">Propose a benchmark, add an official evaluation, correct a result, or report a broken source through structured GitHub forms.</p></header>
  <article class="narrow section prose">
    <div class="grid two"><a class="card" href="https://github.com/SpectrAI-Initiative/bio-benchmark-atlas/issues/new?template=review-paper.yml"><h3>Review a paper →</h3><p>Submit a DOI/preprint plus a legal open or authorized source. The issue becomes a candidate until the owner explicitly starts a local Codex intake.</p></a><a class="card" href="https://github.com/SpectrAI-Initiative/bio-benchmark-atlas/issues/new?template=add-benchmark.yml"><h3>Add benchmark →</h3><p>Creator source, access, counts, taxonomy, and runnable status.</p></a><a class="card" href="https://github.com/SpectrAI-Initiative/bio-benchmark-atlas/issues/new?template=add-evaluation.yml"><h3>Add evaluation →</h3><p>Work, exact model, relationship, scope, metrics, tools, grader, and locators.</p></a><a class="card" href="https://github.com/SpectrAI-Initiative/bio-benchmark-atlas/issues/new?template=correct-metadata.yml"><h3>Correct metadata →</h3><p>Show the current field, proposed value, and primary evidence.</p></a><a class="card" href="https://github.com/SpectrAI-Initiative/bio-benchmark-atlas/issues/new?template=broken-source.yml"><h3>Broken source →</h3><p>Report moved, unavailable, or materially changed canonical sources.</p></a></div>
    <h2>What happens to a submitted paper</h2><ol><li>DOI, preprint ID, canonical URL, title fingerprint, open candidate issues, and recent paper-intake PRs are checked for duplication.</li><li>The source is MIME-checked, capped at 45 MiB / 150 pages, fingerprinted, and read only from an ignored local temporary directory.</li><li>After the owner explicitly selects the paper, a fresh read-only Codex session separates evaluation, training/fine-tuning, validation, model selection, external-result summary, and pure background citations.</li><li>A second fresh Codex session independently rechecks every claim and locator against the original source. Disagreement never becomes a normal field.</li><li>Deterministic code—not either session—assigns IDs and creates Work, BenchmarkUse, Model, and sufficiently complete EvaluationRun records.</li><li>A Ready PR runs normal CI and can merge only after <code>wang422003</code> comments <code>/approve-paper-intake &lt;full-current-head-sha&gt;</code>.</li></ol>
    <h2>Pull request checklist</h2><ul><li>Describe what changed and cite a primary or official source.</li><li>Map Scientific Tasks only from an official taxonomy, formal track, or locatable official artifact; preserve count unit and basis.</li><li>Say whether the evaluation is full, subset, track, or unknown—and include realized <code>n</code> when reported.</li><li>Record metrics, aggregation, tools, repeats, grader, and every remaining unreported field.</li><li>Do not copy benchmark questions, restricted attachments, or third-party papers into this repository.</li><li>Run <code>pnpm registry:validate</code> and <code>pnpm registry:build</code>.</li></ul>
    <h2>Review policy</h2><p>All production changes use pull requests. Paper-intake PRs additionally require the <code>paper-owner-gate</code>: only an exact-SHA approval comment by <code>wang422003</code> passes, and any later push invalidates it. Local Codex never auto-merges. Candidate issues, source files, evidence excerpts, session transcripts, and model drafts are excluded from public exports.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
